SIMPLE: amercement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amercement
<hw>A*merce"ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>amerciment</ets>.]</ety> <def>The infliction of a penalty at the
discretion of the court; also, a mulct or penalty thus imposed. It
differs from a <xex>fine</xex>, in that the latter is, or was
originally, a fixed and certain sum prescribed by statute for an
offense; but an amercement is arbitrary. Hence, the act or practice of
affeering. [See <er>Affeer</er>.]</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word, in old books, is written
<asp>amerciament</asp>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Amercement royal</b></col>, <cd>a penalty imposed on an
officer for a misdemeanor in his office.</cd>
<rj><au>Jacobs.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amercer</ent>⟦br⟧
